# Copy this file to `.env`. It holds only non-secret config (PROVIDER, MODEL);
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Your API key is NOT stored here or in .env — see the "API keys" note lower
# down and ../SECRETS.md. (.env is in .gitignore regardless; never commit it.)
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT: most of this repo needs NO key at all.
#
# Sections 2-7 (the protocol, your first server, the client, resources,
# prompts, a multi-tool server) are fully OFFLINE — an MCP server and client
# talk to each other with no LLM involved. You only need a key for Section 8
# onward, where an LLM (the "host") drives the MCP tools.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# The host (Section 8 + the capstone) is provider-agnostic — pick whichever
# you already set up in a sibling DeepDive.
#
#   openai  -> OpenAI chat + function calling   (needs OPENAI_API_KEY)
#   claude  -> Claude messages + tool use       (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
#
# Default is "openai".
PROVIDER=openai

# --- API keys are NOT stored here ---
# Your key never goes in this file or in .env. Store it in your OS keychain and
# inject it per-command with `secrun` (2-minute setup: ../SECRETS.md), then run
# key-using scripts as:  secrun python examples/...
#   PROVIDER=openai  needs  OPENAI_API_KEY     https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   PROVIDER=claude  needs  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
